{
  "local_port": 46330,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I register my mobile number with UAN?",
  "response": "To register your mobile number with the Universal Account Number (UAN), you'll typically need to follow a few steps. The UAN is a unique 12-digit number assigned to employees covered under the Employees' Provident Fund (EPF) in India. Here's how you can register or update your mobile number with UAN:\n\n### For New Users:\n\n1. **Obtain UAN:**\n   - Your employer should provide you with your UAN. If not, you can check with your employer or find it on your salary slip.\n\n2. **Activate UAN:**\n   - Go to the EPFO member portal: [https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/](https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/).\n   - Click on \"Activate UAN.\"\n   - Enter your UAN, details like member ID, Aadhaar, PAN, etc.\n   - Verify details and enter the Captcha code.\n   - You will receive an OTP on your registered mobile number. Enter the OTP to activate your UAN account.\n\n3. **Register Mobile Number:**\n   - During the activation process, you can register or verify your mobile number.\n   - Ensure that you enter a valid and active mobile number, as this number will be used for future communication and OTPs.\n\n### For Existing Users Wanting to Update Mobile Number:\n\n1. **Log in to the EPFO Portal:**\n   - Visit [https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/](https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/).\n   - Enter your UAN, password, and Captcha to log in.\n\n2. **Access Profile Settings:**\n   - Once logged in, go to \"Manage\" and select \"Contact Details.\"\n\n3. **Update Mobile Number:**\n   - Click on the option to change your mobile number.\n   - Enter the new mobile number.\n   - An OTP will be sent to your new mobile number for verification.\n   - Enter the OTP to confirm and update the new number in your profile.\n\n4. **Save Changes:**\n   - After verification, the new number will be updated, and you'll receive a confirmation message.\n\n### Important Points:\n\n- Ensure that your mobile number is active and accessible to receive OTPs.\n- Keep your UAN and password confidential and do not share them with anyone.\n- If you encounter issues, you can contact your employer or the EPFO helpdesk for assistance.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to register or update your mobile number with your UAN successfully.",
